Removed all 1Hz diagnostic stats timers (HostSession.startStatsTimer/txFrames/txSilentFrames, ClientSession.startSchedStatsTimer/rxCount/schedCount/dropPast, AudioChannel.Receiver.startStatsTimer/rxPackets). Each timer was firing on the same dispatch queue that handles audio broadcast/receive, and `os_log` flushes were briefly blocking the queue causing 10-20ms gaps in audio playback exactly once per second. The timers served their diagnostic purpose (caught the SCStream PTS clock-domain bug) and are no longer needed.